# Storage report

On-disk bytes per corpus scale, both engines — report-class, no clocks. Engine bytes = `data.mdb` (raw after load; compacted via `Db::compact`). `SQLite` parity config: WAL, `synchronous=FULL`, `fullfsync=ON`, 256 MiB cache, prepared statements in 4096-row transactions; indexed lane = full DDL + family indexes + ANALYZE; table-only lane = index-free STRICT tables, no ANALYZE. Every file statted after a truncating WAL checkpoint with the connection dropped; wal bytes are reported so an uncheckpointed emission is visible. facts = writable-relation rows (closed vocabularies excluded). seed 1.

